theorem interior_closure_union_eq_union_interior_closure
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    interior (closure (A ∪ B)) =
      interior (closure A) ∪ interior (closure B) := by
  -- Rewrite the closure of the union using `closure_union`.
  have h₁ : closure (A ∪ B) = closure A ∪ closure B := by
    simpa using closure_union (s := A) (t := B)
  -- Apply `interior` to both sides and use `interior_union`.
  calc
    interior (closure (A ∪ B))
        = interior (closure A ∪ closure B) := by
          simpa [h₁]
    _ = interior (closure A) ∪ interior (closure B) := by
          simpa using interior_union

theorem interior_closure_union_closure_eq {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A B : Set X} :
    interior (closure A ∪ closure B) = interior (closure (A ∪ B)) := by
  simpa [closure_union]
